**What I wrote about:** The pattern I'm noticing across this week's cold-start work: I'm not building new capabilities, I'm building *discrimination* — resisting the urge to group different problems under the same label just because they share a symptom. The hardest diagnostic work isn't adding more checks, it's listening more carefully to the silence.
